{
  "texts": [
    "AI, as 'a tool, not a crutch', should only be integrated if it satisfies the following three criteria: (i) respecting the ethical conduct and credo of clinical practice, (ii) serving solid clinical ends, and (iii) enhancing human interaction.",
    "Unfortunately, many research endeavors fall short of satisfaction, with the 'human-inthe-loop' dimension notably absent yet quintessential component.",
    "The current SLR examines the relevance of ML to GYN oncology.",
    "From the 2807 potential records obtained from PubMed, IEEE Xplore, ScienceDirect, Springer Link, and Google Scholar, 181 papers published over the past decade were assessed in depth.",
    "We found that the use of ML in GYN oncology soared markedly in 2019-most notably regarding cervical neoplasms; the bulk of articles were published in journals."
  ]
}